## 4. Runtime Integrity & Anti‑Tamper Controls

| Control | Implementation | Security Benefit |
|---------|----------------|------------------|
| **App‑side checksum verification** | Embed a SHA‑256 hash of the signed APK/IPA in the app and verify it at launch (using the OS‑provided verification API). | Detects post‑install binary modification. |
| **Google Play App Signing / Apple App Store notarization** | Use the platform’s code‑signing service; enforce **App Transport Security (ATS)** on iOS. | Guarantees the binary delivered to users matches the publisher’s signature. |
| **AWS Lambda code signing** | Sign the deployment package with AWS Signer and enforce `CodeSigningConfig` on the function. | Prevents malicious code injection into the backend. |
| **Amazon Inspector (ECR scanning)** | Scan container images (if any) for known ViperRAT signatures before deployment. | Early detection of compromised images. |
| **Runtime Application Self‑Protection (RASP)** | Add a lightweight RASP library (e.g., **Sqreen**, **Signal Sciences**) to the mobile app to monitor for suspicious system calls (e.g., opening a socket to unknown C2). | Blocks malicious behavior even if the binary is compromised. |

All of the above are **defense‑in‑depth** and do not rely on a single point of failure.

