## 1. Immediate Cloud‑Security Remediation Checklist (AWS‑focused)

| # | Action | Why it matters | How to implement (secure‑by‑design) |
|---|--------|----------------|--------------------------------------|
| 1 | **Rotate all IAM access keys** that have been used in the last 30 days. | Stolen keys are the primary foothold. | Use the AWS CLI/Console to **deactivate** then **delete** old keys, generate new ones, and update only the required services. Do **not** embed keys in code or config files. |
