| 8 | **Search for hard‑coded credentials** in source repositories (GitHub, GitLab, Bitbucket). | Prevent future credential leakage. | Run **GitGuardian**, **TruffleHog**, or AWS **CodeGuru** scans. Immediately revoke any exposed keys. |
| 9 | **Isolate compromised resources** (EC2, Lambda, IAM roles) by removing them from production VPCs or attaching a **quarantine security group**. | Stops further data exfiltration while you investigate. | Use the AWS console or CLI to change the **network ACL** or **security group** to deny all outbound traffic. |
